Claims:
[
    "In PbLi DCLL liquid metal breeder blankets, the mainstream tritium extraction technologies are Vacuum Permeator and Gas Bubbling.",
    "Both Vacuum Permeator and Gas Bubbling utilize the high solubility and mobility of tritium in PbLi.",
    "Vacuum Permeator and Gas Bubbling face key challenges in efficiency and engineering implementation, including permeation losses, retention, and material compatibility.",
    "The challenges faced by Vacuum Permeator and Gas Bubbling need to be addressed through material optimization and process integration.",
    "The PbLi DCLL blanket uses liquid lead-lithium (PbLi) alloy as both a tritium breeder and a partial coolant, serving dual roles in neutron multiplication and tritium production.",
    "DCLL stands for Dual-Coolant Lead-Lithium, indicating that the blanket and first wall are cooled by separate helium and PbLi circuits.",
    "The Tritium Extraction System (TES) efficiently separates and recovers tritium generated in liquid PbLi to ensure fuel cycle closure and environmental safety.",
    "Vacuum Permeator operates by having PbLi flow through high-permeability metal tubes (such as Ta, V, Zr) in a vacuum environment at high temperatures.",
    "In Vacuum Permeator, tritium atoms diffuse from PbLi to the tube wall, permeate through the metal, enter the vacuum inside the tube, and are then pumped out by vacuum pumps for collection.",
    "Key parameters for Vacuum Permeator include operating temperature (typically 500-600°C), tube material permeability, PbLi flow rate, and vacuum level.",
    "The Vacuum Permeator process involves PbLi exiting the blanket, flowing through the permeator, tritium passing through the tube wall, being extracted from the vacuum side, and PbLi returning to the cycle.",
    "Gas Bubbling operates by injecting inert gases (such as He, Ar) into PbLi to form bubbles, transferring tritium from PbLi to the bubbles.",
    "In Gas Bubbling, tritium is carried out by the gas flow to a gas-liquid separator for extraction.",
    "Key parameters for Gas Bubbling include bubble size, gas flow rate, contact time, temperature, and pressure.",
    "The Gas Bubbling process involves PbLi exiting the blanket, gas bubbling, tritium-rich gas, gas-liquid separation, tritium extraction, and PbLi returning to the cycle.",
    "Vacuum Permeator achieves high extraction rates with high tritium recovery rates and is suitable for large-scale continuous processing.",
    "Vacuum Permeator is limited by the corrosion resistance and high-temperature stability of the permeable membrane materials.",
    "Gas Bubbling is simple in process and suitable for local or auxiliary extraction.",
    "Gas Bubbling efficiency is affected by the contact interface between bubbles and PbLi, tritium partition coefficient, and requires preventing bubble entrainment of PbLi to avoid safety issues.",
    "PbLi is highly corrosive to common metals, requiring permeable membranes to have both high tritium permeability and excellent resistance to PbLi corrosion (e.g., Ta, V, Fe alloys).",
    "Materials for permeable membranes are costly and difficult to manufacture and maintain.",
    "Gas bubbling requires system sealing and prevention of PbLi carryover to avoid metal oxidation and system blockage.",
    "Under high temperature, high pressure, and strong corrosion conditions, tritium extraction systems require high reliability, redundancy, and online monitoring to prevent tritium leakage and system failure.",
    "Tritium gas separation and purification require multi-stage processes to ensure the purity and safety of the tritium fuel cycle.",
    "Large-scale continuous operation requires handling huge PbLi flow rates and high tritium fluxes, imposing extremely high demands on equipment lifespan and maintenance cycles.",
    "Tritium easily penetrates structural materials and escapes into coolants or vacuum chambers, causing tritium losses and safety hazards.",
    "Solutions to tritium permeation losses include developing efficient anti-permeation coatings (e.g., alumina, ceramic films), optimizing structural material selection (low tritium permeability alloys), and enhancing sealing of blankets and cooling circuits.",
    "PbLi has high solubility for tritium; if circulation rates or extraction efficiency are insufficient, tritium accumulation in PbLi occurs, affecting the Tritium Breeding Ratio (TBR) and safety.",
    "Solutions to tritium retention in PbLi include optimizing PbLi circulation rates, improving TES extraction capacity, and implementing online tritium monitoring and dynamic regulation.",
    "An efficient and reliable tritium extraction system is a core element for achieving fuel self-sufficiency, environmental safety, and stable operation in PbLi liquid blankets for fusion reactors.",
    "Achieving an efficient and reliable tritium extraction system requires multidisciplinary integration of materials, thermal engineering, systems engineering, and safety control technologies.",
    "In PbLi DCLL blankets, tritium extraction relies primarily on Vacuum Permeator and Gas Bubbling technologies.",
    "Key engineering challenges for tritium extraction include improving extraction efficiency, suppressing tritium permeation and retention, and overcoming material corrosion and system integration issues.",
    "Tritium extraction is one of the technical bottlenecks for the engineering of fusion reactors."
] 

